&gt; On 8/5/07, dmugtasimov &lt;dimasoft2001@... 
&gt; &lt;mailto:dimasoft2001%40mail.ru&gt;&gt; wrote:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Imagine that there is a class Algorithm and its subclassed Algorithm1,
&gt;  &gt; Algorithm2, .. Algorithm9. All AlgorithmN classes have the same
&gt;  &gt; contract (thus they have same methods and these method should supply
&gt;  &gt; the same output for the same input).
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; public abstract Algorithm {
&gt;  &gt; public abstract String calculate(String in);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; public Algorithm1 {
&gt;  &gt; public String calculate(String in) {
&gt;  &gt; ... method body 1...
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; public Algorithm2 {
&gt;  &gt; public String calculate(String in) {
&gt;  &gt; ... method body 2...
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; and so on up to 9.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; There is test case AlgorithmTestCase extends TestCase.
&gt;  &gt; public AlgorithmTestCase extends TestCase {
&gt;  &gt; public void testAlgorithm() {
&gt;  &gt; Algorithm algorithm = ... Algorithm1..Algorithm9 instance creation
&gt;  &gt; code ...;
&gt;  &gt; assertEquals(&quot;RESULT1&quot;, algorithm.calculate(&quot;INPUT1&quot;));
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Is it possible using JUnit and how to run AlgorithmTestCase meeting
&gt;  &gt; the following conditions?
&gt;  &gt; 1. Each instance of AlgorithmTestCase does test only one Algorithm
&gt;  &gt; subclass.
&gt;  &gt; 2. AlgorithmTestCase is run against each Algorithm subclass.
&gt;  &gt; 3. GUI runner is started only once.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; I tried to do that by passing subclass name in system properties, but
&gt;  &gt; failed. It happens because when I add test case by
&gt;  &gt; suite.addTestSuite(Class ...) the actual of TestCase is created after
&gt;  &gt; the last test case is added, so system properties contain the last
&gt;  &gt; supplied value.
